WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.240
I know we've all seen the trend of the football boyfriend bingo, and if you want to play too

00:00:04.240 --> 00:00:08.960
and practice your code at the same time, it's not that hard to build using Shiny for Python.

00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:13.540
This game requires a few things, generating the rules for bingo, a bingo board, a way

00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:16.520
to mark the cards as complete, and a fun modal when you win.

00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:19.200
First, we need a place to create the rules for each of the cards.

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:21.320
We need a text input and a submit button.

00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:22.840
Next, we need to create the bingo cards.

00:00:22.840 --> 00:00:25.840
This is nothing more than a card component that reads from our inputs.

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:28.719
Then we can turn the cards into buttons that track whether this element has been clicked

00:00:28.719 --> 00:00:29.719
or not.

00:00:29.719 --> 00:00:32.240
Finally, we need to track the bingo status using some basic logic.

00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:34.639
And then you can play boyfriend bingo all season long.

00:00:34.639 --> 00:00:36.119
Make sure to follow for more data science content.

00:00:36.119 --> 00:00:36.619
Bye!

